{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Exo|1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","chapter":1,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":1,"text":"These are the names of the sons of Israel who came to Egypt with Jacob; each came with his family:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":2,"text":"Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":3,"text":"Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":4,"text":"Dan and Naphtali; Gad and Asher.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":5,"text":"The total number of Jacob’s descendants was seventy; Joseph was already in Egypt.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":6,"text":"Joseph and all his brothers and all that generation eventually died.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":7,"text":"But the Israelites were fruitful, increased rapidly, multiplied, and became extremely numerous so that the land was filled with them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":8,"text":"A new king, who did not know about Joseph, came to power in Egypt.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":9,"text":"He said to his people, “Look, the Israelite people are more numerous and powerful than we are.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":10,"text":"Come, let’s deal shrewdly with them; otherwise they will multiply further, and when war breaks out, they will join our enemies, fight against us, and leave the country.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":11,"text":"So the Egyptians assigned taskmasters over the Israelites to oppress them with forced labor. They built Pithom and Rameses as supply cities for Pharaoh.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":12,"text":"But the more they oppressed them, the more they multiplied and spread so that the Egyptians came to dread the Israelites.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":13,"text":"They worked the Israelites ruthlessly","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":14,"text":"and made their lives bitter with difficult labor in brick and mortar and in all kinds of fieldwork. They ruthlessly imposed all this work on them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":15,"text":"The king of Egypt said to the Hebrew midwives —the first, whose name was Shiphrah, and the second, whose name was Puah —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":16,"text":"“When you help the Hebrew women give birth, observe them as they deliver. If the child is a son, kill him, but if it’s a daughter, she may live.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":17,"text":"The midwives, however, feared God and did not do as the king of Egypt had told them; they let the boys live.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":18,"text":"So the king of Egypt summoned the midwives and asked them, “Why have you done this and let the boys live?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":19,"text":"The midwives said to Pharaoh, “The Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women, for they are vigorous and give birth before the midwife can get to them.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":20,"text":"So God was good to the midwives, and the people multiplied and became very numerous.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":21,"text":"Since the midwives feared God, he gave them families.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","bookOrder":1,"chapter":1,"verse":22,"text":"Pharaoh then commanded all his people, “You must throw every son born to the Hebrews into the Nile, but let every daughter live.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Exo","chapter":1,"paragraphStarts":[1,2,3,4,5,6,8,15,19,20],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Israel Oppressed in Egypt"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"These are the names of the sons of Israel who came to Egypt with Jacob; each came with his family: "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 46:8","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":8,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 46:8","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":8}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Dan and Naphtali; Gad and Asher."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The total number of Jacob’s descendants "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit of people issuing from Jacob’s loins"},{"kind":"text","text":" was seventy; "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"LXX, DSS read 75; Gn 46:27; Ac 7:14"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 46:26–27","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":26,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 10:22","book":"Deu","chapter":10,"verse":22,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Joseph was already in Egypt."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 46:26–27","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":26},{"label":"Dt 10:22","book":"Deu","chapter":10,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit of people issuing from Jacob’s loins"},{"marker":2,"text":"LXX, DSS read 75; Gn 46:27; Ac 7:14"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Joseph and all his brothers and all that generation eventually died. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 50:26","book":"Gen","chapter":50,"verse":26,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 50:26","book":"Gen","chapter":50,"verse":26}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But the Israelites were fruitful, increased rapidly, multiplied, and became extremely numerous "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 12:2","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 46:3","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 26:5","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":5,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:17","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":17,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that the land was filled with them."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 12:2","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":2},{"label":"Gn 46:3","book":"Gen","chapter":46,"verse":3},{"label":"Dt 26:5","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":5},{"label":"Ac 7:17","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"A new king, who did not know about Joseph, came to power in Egypt. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He said to his people, “Look, the Israelite people are more numerous and powerful than we are. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 105:24","book":"Psa","chapter":105,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 105:24","book":"Psa","chapter":105,"verse":24}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Come, let’s deal shrewdly with them; otherwise they will multiply further, and when war breaks out, they will join our enemies, fight against us, and leave the country.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 83:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":83,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:19","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 83:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":83,"verse":3},{"label":"Ac 7:19","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So the Egyptians assigned taskmasters over the Israelites to oppress them with forced labor. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 15:13","book":"Gen","chapter":15,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 2:11","book":"Exo","chapter":2,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 3:7","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 5:4–5","book":"Exo","chapter":5,"verse":4,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 6:6","book":"Exo","chapter":6,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 26:6","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":6,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" They built Pithom and Rameses as supply cities "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 47:11","book":"Gen","chapter":47,"verse":11,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 9:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":9,"verse":19,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 8:4","book":"2Ch","chapter":8,"verse":4,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" for Pharaoh. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 15:13","book":"Gen","chapter":15,"verse":13},{"label":"Ex 2:11","book":"Exo","chapter":2,"verse":11},{"label":"Ex 3:7","book":"Exo","chapter":3,"verse":7},{"label":"Ex 5:4–5","book":"Exo","chapter":5,"verse":4},{"label":"Ex 6:6","book":"Exo","chapter":6,"verse":6},{"label":"Dt 26:6","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":6},{"label":"Gn 47:11","book":"Gen","chapter":47,"verse":11},{"label":"1Kg 9:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":9,"verse":19},{"label":"2Ch 8:4","book":"2Ch","chapter":8,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But the more they oppressed them, the more they multiplied and spread so that the Egyptians came to dread "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or Egyptians loathed"},{"kind":"text","text":" the Israelites. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or Egyptians loathed"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They worked the Israelites ruthlessly "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 4:20","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 4:20","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and made their lives bitter with difficult labor in brick and mortar and in all kinds of fieldwork. They ruthlessly imposed all this work on them. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 2:23","book":"Exo","chapter":2,"verse":23,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 20:15","book":"Num","chapter":20,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:19","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":19,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 2:23","book":"Exo","chapter":2,"verse":23},{"label":"Nm 20:15","book":"Num","chapter":20,"verse":15},{"label":"Ac 7:19","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The king of Egypt said to the Hebrew midwives —the first, whose name was Shiphrah, and the second, whose name was Puah — "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“When you help the Hebrew women give birth, observe them as they deliver. If the child is a son, kill him, but if it’s a daughter, she may live.” "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The midwives, however, feared God "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 1:21","book":"Exo","chapter":1,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 16:6","book":"Pro","chapter":16,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and did not do as the king of Egypt had told them; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dn 3:16","book":"Dan","chapter":3,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 4:18–20","book":"Act","chapter":4,"verse":18,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 5:29","book":"Act","chapter":5,"verse":29,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" they let the boys live. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 1:21","book":"Exo","chapter":1,"verse":21},{"label":"Pr 16:6","book":"Pro","chapter":16,"verse":6},{"label":"Dn 3:16","book":"Dan","chapter":3,"verse":16},{"label":"Ac 4:18–20","book":"Act","chapter":4,"verse":18},{"label":"Ac 5:29","book":"Act","chapter":5,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So the king of Egypt summoned the midwives and asked them, “Why have you done this and let the boys live?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The midwives said to Pharaoh, “The Hebrew women are not like the Egyptian women, for they are vigorous and give birth before the midwife can get to them.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 2:4","book":"Jos","chapter":2,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 17:20","book":"2Sa","chapter":17,"verse":20,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 2:4","book":"Jos","chapter":2,"verse":4},{"label":"2Sm 17:20","book":"2Sa","chapter":17,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So God was good to the midwives, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 11:18","book":"Pro","chapter":11,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 3:10","book":"Isa","chapter":3,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the people multiplied and became very numerous. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Pr 11:18","book":"Pro","chapter":11,"verse":18},{"label":"Is 3:10","book":"Isa","chapter":3,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Since the midwives feared God, he gave them families. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 2:35","book":"1Sa","chapter":2,"verse":35,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 7:11","book":"2Sa","chapter":7,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 7:27","book":"2Sa","chapter":7,"verse":27,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:38","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":38,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 127:1","book":"Psa","chapter":127,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 2:35","book":"1Sa","chapter":2,"verse":35},{"label":"2Sm 7:11","book":"2Sa","chapter":7,"verse":11},{"label":"2Sm 7:27","book":"2Sa","chapter":7,"verse":27},{"label":"1Kg 11:38","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":38},{"label":"Ps 127:1","book":"Psa","chapter":127,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Exo:1:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Pharaoh then commanded all his people, “You must throw every son born to the Hebrews into the Nile, but let every daughter live.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 41:1","book":"Gen","chapter":41,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:19","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":19,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 41:1","book":"Gen","chapter":41,"verse":1},{"label":"Ac 7:19","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783279316297}